          This is the last token that has been consumed successfully. If this object has been created due to a parse error, the token followng this token will (therefore) be the first error token.

          Each entry in this array is an array of integers. Each array of integers represents a sequence of tokens (by their ordinal values) that is expected at this point of the parse.

          This is the last token that has been consumed successfully. If this object has been created due to a parse error, the token followng this token will (therefore) be the first error token.

          DataRecordNature nature
          Metadata nature should correspond with graph nature, see DataRecordMetadata.checkConfig(ConfigurationStatus). Different implementations of DataRecord are used for various natures. Nature DataRecordNature.DATA_RECORD is represented by DataRecord. Nature DataRecordNature.TOKEN is represented by Token. Record nature is by default derived from graph nature. The GraphNature#ETL_GRAPH corresponds with DataRecordNature.DATA_RECORD and the GraphNature#JOBFLOW corresponds with DataRecordNature.TOKEN.
